bilingual.source: Visitors enter Chinatown through the legendary Dragon Gate.

bilingual.source: Then the spaceship will re-enter the Earth's atmosphere.

bilingual.source: Jamal and the genie enter the stage and stand on the right.

list.abstract: 回车键，又称确认键、输入键，在Windows系统的叫做“Enter”，在macOS中则叫做“return”，是用以代表换行的控制码之一。其位置在引号键的右边，另一个位置在数字键盘的右下角。回车键的另一个作用是确认输入的执行命令。
enter，英文单词，主要用作为及物动词、不及物动词、名词，作及物动词时意为“进入；开始；参加”，作不及物动词时意为“参加，登场；进去”，作名词时意为“ [计]输入；回车，人名；(英)恩特”。

yingyinNormal.en: When you enter the door, you enter the room, and every time you click in a room, you got a certain pay off.
yingyinNormal.zh: 当你点开一扇门，你会进入一个房间，每次你点击一扇门后你会得到一定的分数。

yingyinNormal.en: You have no right, no right to enter that mountain. I have the only right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 你无权，无权进入孤山。只有我有权利。

yingyinNormal.en: To understand what's happening, you need to enter a complex and microscopic world.
yingyinNormal.zh: 要想弄明白光合作用原理，我们需要进入一个显微镜下的复杂世界。

yingyinNormal.en: Okay. So, to get the ledger, one of us needs to enter the torus and change the security profile.
yingyinNormal.zh: 好吧，所以，要想拿到账册，必须有一个人进入那个圆环体替换掉其中安全资料。

yingyinNormal.en: New technological advances have seen them enter the space race with the US and Russia for the first time.
yingyinNormal.zh: 新技术的进步见证着中国进入太空竞赛的脚步，和美国、俄罗斯同台竞艺。

yingyinNormal.en: The Hermes. Well, they, it can't enter Mars orbit. Otherwise, they will never have enough fuel to, make it home.
yingyinNormal.zh: 赫尔墨斯号不能进入火星的轨道，要不他们就没有足够的燃料回家了。

yingyinNormal.en: Brain function in the dream will be about 20 times normal. And when you enter a dream within that dream, the effect is compounded.
yingyinNormal.zh: 梦空间的脑部运作比平时约快20倍，当你进入梦中梦 运作速度亦倍增。

yingyinNormal.en: Enter the Federal Aviation Administration, or FAA, which maintains our complex flight-management system today. Here's how it works.
yingyinNormal.zh: 进入联邦导航系统，它包括了我们现代复杂的航空管理系统，则是它的运作方式。

yingyinNormal.en: Oh, I'm afraid not. Section seven here, on the right to enter the bathroom in emergency situations, is not specific as to what constitutes an emergency.
yingyinNormal.zh: 恐怕是的，第七部分这里，紧急情况下进入洗手间的权利，没有明确约定什么是紧急情况。

yingyinNormal.en: Will you promise never to enter into such an engagement?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你愿意答应我，永远不跟他订婚吗？

yingyinNormal.en: Step two, enter our apartment. Step three, enter my bedroom. Step four.
yingyinNormal.zh: 第二步，走进我们的房子，第三步...走进我的房间，第四步...

yingyinNormal.en: I'll wager there are ways to enter that town unseen. Aye.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我打赌肯定有悄悄进城的方法。对。

yingyinNormal.en: She wouldn't let me enter the library while you met him. So that was you?
yingyinNormal.zh: 你在书房跟他面试，她还把我挡在了外面，那是你啊？

yingyinNormal.en: Correct. You've passed the first barrier to roommate hood. You may enter.
yingyinNormal.zh: 正确，你已通过室友关系第一关，你可以进来了。

yingyinNormal.en: It did enter my mind. But then something happened that made it, shoot right out.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我想过啊，但后来的事让这个念头飞了。

yingyinNormal.en: We'll enter his subconscious and find out what he doesn't want you to know. All right.
yingyinNormal.zh: 我们潜入他潜意识找出当中所隐瞒，好。

yingyinNormal.en: I want to enter her in a baby beauty pageant. Oh, my God. That's the creepiest thing I've ever heard.
yingyinNormal.zh: 嗯，我想让她参加婴儿选美。哦，天哪，这是我听说过的最奇怪的事情。

yingyinNormal.en: Escape the heat and enter a world of color at the Singapore Botanic Gardens and National Orchid Garden.
yingyinNormal.zh: 在缤纷的新加坡植物园和新加坡国家胡姬园，能让人避开炎热的天气。

yingyinNormal.en: Chrissy, I need to discuss something with you. Please come to my office at 1:00 p.M., enter quietly, and sit down at my desk.
yingyinNormal.zh: "克里斯，我要和你谈谈，请下午一点到我办公室来悄悄进来，在桌边坐下"。

yingyinNormal.en: As 2014 comes to an end, we can enter the New Year with new confidence that America is making significant strides where it counts.
yingyinNormal.zh: 2014年马上就要结束了，我们怀着信心走进新的一年，美国在体现她价值的地方，正发生着显著的变化。

examination_example.sentence: Pairs of opponents hit the ball back and forth until one winner emerges from all who <highlight>entered</highlight>.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 成对的对手来回击球，直到所有参赛者中出现一名胜利者。

examination_example.sentence: The "Ruby on Rails" language they learned may not even be relevant by the time they <highlight>enter</highlight> the job market.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们所学的“Ruby on Rails”语言甚至可能在他们进入就业市场的时候已经不相关了。

examination_example.sentence: Women <highlight>entering</highlight> top management become headlines.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 女性参与高层管理成为头条新闻。

examination_example.sentence: As fewer such workers <highlight>enter</highlight> the country, the characteristics of the agricultural workforce are changing.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 随着进入该国的此类工人越来越少，农业劳动力的特征正在发生变化。

examination_example.sentence: But exploring one's smartphone is more like <highlight>entering</highlight> his or her home.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 但是探索一个人的智能手机更像是进入他或她的家。

examination_example.sentence: In many respects, the U.S. was more socially tolerant <highlight>entering</highlight> this recession than at any time in its history.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在许多方面，美国进入这次经济衰退时，比其历史上任何时候都更加社会宽容。

examination_example.sentence: You've heard that plastic is polluting the oceans—between 4.8 and 12.7 million tones <highlight>enter</highlight> ocean ecosystems every year.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 你听说过塑料正在污染海洋——每年有480万到1270万吨塑料进入海洋生态系统。

examination_example.sentence: And MP3 players, smart phones, and LCD TVs <highlight>entered</highlight> homes in 2002, before tablets and e-readers showed up in 2007.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 在2007年平板电脑和电子阅读器出现之前，MP3播放器、智能手机和液晶电视于2002年进入家庭。

examination_example.sentence: They did very well this season and so <highlight>entered</highlight> a tournament, which normally was only for more skilled club teams.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 他们本赛季表现非常好，因此进入了锦标赛，这通常只对更有技术的俱乐部球队开放。

examination_example.sentence: Depending on the kind of race you plan to <highlight>enter</highlight>, you can set up a timetable for the remaining weeks before the race.
examination_example.sentence_trans: 根据你计划参加的比赛类型，你可以在比赛前为剩下的几周制定时间表。
